(1, 1, 4, 0, 'GrokBB Help', 1459545094, 1467697714, 0, '<h3>Welcome to the official GrokBB Help!</h3>\n<p>We will eventually get some HowTos and FAQs up here, but for now please feel free to post questions related to general site usage or board administration. We will answer you as soon as possible.</p>\n<p>If you have suggestions for new features, want to view our roadmap, or would like to report a bug then please do that over in <a href="https://www.grokbb.com/g/GrokBB_Dev">GrokBB Dev</a>.</p>\n<p>Your user experience is our top priority, and we''re always striving to provide you with friendly, easy to understand feedback and support. Please let us know how we can help you, and thank you for visiting!</p>\n', '### Welcome to the official GrokBB Help!\n\nWe will eventually get some HowTos and FAQs up here, but for now please feel free to post questions related to general site usage or board administration. We will answer you as soon as possible.\n\nIf you have suggestions for new features, want to view our roadmap, or would like to report a bug then please do that over in [GrokBB Dev](https://www.grokbb.com/g/GrokBB_Dev).\n\nYour user experience is our top priority, and we''re always striving to provide you with friendly, easy to understand feedback and support. Please let us know how we can help you, and thank you for visiting!', 1, 1, 'The official GrokBB help documentation and support.', 'GrokBB', 'help', '', '0', 0, '', 4, 0, 2, 1),
(2, 1, 4, 0, 'GrokBB Dev', 1459554039, 1467697459, 0, '<h3>Welcome to the official GrokBB Dev!</h3>\n<p>Here you can discuss the inner workings of GrokBB, request new features, view our roadmap and submit bug reports.</p>\n<p>Please review the following topics before posting.</p>\n<ul><li><a href="https://www.grokbb.com/g/GrokBB_Dev/view/1">GrokBB Roadmap</a></li>\n<li><a href="https://www.grokbb.com/g/GrokBB_Dev/view/10">Bug Reporting Guidelines</a></li>\n</ul>', '### Welcome to the official GrokBB Dev!\n\nHere you can discuss the inner workings of GrokBB, request new features, view our roadmap and submit bug reports.\n\nPlease review the following topics before posting.\n\n* [GrokBB Roadmap](https://www.grokbb.com/g/GrokBB_Dev/view/1)\n* [Bug Reporting Guidelines](https://www.grokbb.com/g/GrokBB_Dev/view/10)', 1, 1, 'The official GrokBB development community. Discuss new features, report bugs, and review our roadmap.', 'GrokBB', '', '', '0', 0, '', 6, 0, 31, 49),
(3, 5, 4, 0, 'Music', 1466120907, 1467134106, 1468712907, '<p><strong>/g/Music</strong><br />\nThe board for all your music discussion!</p>\n<p><strong>Rules</strong></p>\n<ol><li>Follow the sidewide rules, duh.</li>\n<li>That''s all the rules for now.</li>\n</ol><p>Also, this is the first board not created by an admin and third overall so that''s cool I guess. </p>\n', '**/g/Music**\nThe board for all your music discussion!\n\n**Rules**\n1. Follow the sidewide rules, duh.\n2. That''s all the rules for now.\n\nAlso, this is the first board not created by an admin and third overall so that''s cool I guess. ', 0, 0, 'Ceci n''est pas une musique board', 'Music', 'Entertainment', 'Sound', '0', 0, '', 3, 3, 3, 12),
(4, 33, 4, 0, 'Exit System Call', 1466139085, 1467701553, 1468731085, '<p>We will be discussing modern hacking techniques under the following categories. We welcome any experience level, but please introduce yourself first, by posting under <strong> Hello, My Name Is </strong> and listing the experience you do have.</p>\n<h4><strong> A/V Signal Test </strong></h4>\n<p>Technical discussions on audio / video formats, media server setup guides, and general news on upcoming movies, tv shows and music.</p>\n<h4><strong> Applied Cryptography </strong></h4>\n<p>For serious discussions and beginners a like.<br />\nWe welcome puzzles and challenges too.</p>\n<h4><strong> DRM Removal &amp; RE </strong></h4>\n<p>The latest DRM removal techniques for books, videos and music. As well as discussions around reverse engineering and the related tools and techniques.</p>\n<h4><strong> Hardware / Gadget Mods </strong></h4>\n<p>Physical device hacking, like consoles, gadgets, chips, lock picking and more ...</p>\n<h4><strong> Hello, My Name Is </strong></h4>\n<p>Please introduce yourself to the community.</p>\n<h4><strong> Member Projects </strong></h4>\n<p>Discuss personal projects and recruit help.</p>\n<h4><strong> Phreaking &amp; Mobile </strong></h4>\n<p>Modern phreaking techniques, VOIP and mobile network / hardware hacking.</p>\n<h4><strong> Secure Communication </strong></h4>\n<p>The tools required for secure communication.<br />\nDiscussions on apps, protocols, and techniques for achieving privacy in an Orwellian world.</p>\n<h4><strong> Tools of the Trade </strong></h4>\n<p>Operating systems, programming languages, apps and related tutorials. Share your expertise, your workflows, and your reviews.</p>\n<h4><strong> Unauthorized Access </strong></h4>\n<p>Intrusion techniques, privilege escalation, default password lists, lockdown HOW-TOs and more ...</p>\n<h4><strong> Zines / Art / Inspiration </strong></h4>\n<p>Modern hacking magazines, recommended reading lists and artistic endeavors.</p>\n', 'We will be discussing modern hacking techniques under the following categories. We welcome any experience level, but please introduce yourself first, by posting under ** Hello, My Name Is ** and listing the experience you do have.\n\n#### ** A/V Signal Test **\nTechnical discussions on audio / video formats, media server setup guides, and general news on upcoming movies, tv shows and music.\n\n#### ** Applied Cryptography **\nFor serious discussions and beginners a like.\nWe welcome puzzles and challenges too.\n\n#### ** DRM Removal & RE **\nThe latest DRM removal techniques for books, videos and music. As well as discussions around reverse engineering and the related tools and techniques.\n\n#### ** Hardware / Gadget Mods **\nPhysical device hacking, like consoles, gadgets, chips, lock picking and more ...\n\n#### ** Hello, My Name Is **\nPlease introduce yourself to the community.\n\n#### ** Member Projects **\nDiscuss personal projects and recruit help.\n\n#### ** Phreaking & Mobile **\nModern phreaking techniques, VOIP and mobile network / hardware hacking.\n\n#### ** Secure Communication **\nThe tools required for secure communication.\nDiscussions on apps, protocols, and techniques for achieving privacy in an Orwellian world.\n\n#### ** Tools of the Trade **\nOperating systems, programming languages, apps and related tutorials. Share your expertise, your workflows, and your reviews.\n\n#### ** Unauthorized Access **\nIntrusion techniques, privilege escalation, default password lists, lockdown HOW-TOs and more ...\n\n#### ** Zines / Art / Inspiration **\nModern hacking magazines, recommended reading lists and artistic endeavors.', 1, 1, 'Hacking in the Modern Age', 'hacking', '', '', '0', 0, '', 3, 0, 0, 0),
(5, 1, 4, 0, 'GrokBB Off Topic', 1466152726, 1467697742, 1468744726, '<h3>Welcome to the official GrokBB Off Topic!</h3>\n<p>Feel free to discuss anything you want here, until we gain more momentum and have more boards created.</p>\n', '### Welcome to the official GrokBB Off Topic!\n\nFeel free to discuss anything you want here, until we gain more momentum and have more boards created.', 1, 1, 'The official Off Topic board for GrokBB. Feel free to discuss anything you want here, while this place grows.', 'GrokBB', '', '', '0', 0, '', 3, 0, 5, 13),
(6, 6, 4, 0, 'SheBangs Junkyard', 1466371755, 1467131726, 1468963755, '<p>Welcome to <strong>SheBang''s Junkyard</strong>, we will remain opened during the beta testing stage of GrokBB or until the trial period expires, whichever comes first. This is a testing board meant for personal usage but feel free to post too.</p>\n<p><strong>SheBang''s Junkyard</strong> is using an experimental mobile friendly CSS, feel free to report any bugs you find in it.</p>\n', 'Welcome to **SheBang''s Junkyard**, we will remain opened during the beta testing stage of GrokBB or until the trial period expires, whichever comes first. This is a testing board meant for personal usage but feel free to post too.\n\n**SheBang''s Junkyard** is using an experimental mobile friendly CSS, feel free to report any bugs you find in it.', 1, 0, 'Now with 89% 96% more mobile friendliness!', 'test', 'board', 'meta', '0', 0, '', 1, 6, 5, 8),
(7, 37, 4, 0, 'Open Source Projects', 1467100976, 1467332058, 1469692976, '<p>A place to share interesting, open source projects or recruit volunteers for your own project.</p>\n', 'A place to share interesting, open source projects or recruit volunteers for your own project.', 1, 0, 'Interesting, open source projects and the people behind them. Promote your software, recruit developers and more ...', '', '', '', '0', 0, '', 3, 0, 0, 0),
(8, 39, 4, 0, 'Spaceship Zero', 1467333733, 1467362540, 1469925733, '<p>From the latest advances in science and technology to the weird and unexplainable. Let''s discuss ...</p>\n<ul><li>Art</li>\n<li>Computers</li>\n<li>Medicine</li>\n<li>Paranormal</li>\n<li>Robots / Cybernetics</li>\n<li>Science From All Realms</li>\n<li>Space &amp; Exploration</li>\n<li>Technology &amp; Recent Advances</li>\n<li>The Mind / Psychology</li>\n</ul><p>Science Fiction literature representing any of these topics are welcome too!</p>\n', 'From the latest advances in science and technology to the weird and unexplainable. Let''s discuss ...\n\n* Art\n* Computers\n* Medicine\n* Paranormal\n* Robots / Cybernetics\n* Science From All Realms\n* Space & Exploration\n* Technology & Recent Advances\n* The Mind / Psychology\n\nScience Fiction literature representing any of these topics are welcome too!\n', 1, 0, 'Exploring all realms of science and the paranormal', 'Science', 'Paranormal', '', '0', 0, '', 4, 0, 0, 0),
