INSERT INTO `gbb_reply` (`id`, `id_tc`, `id_ry`, `id_ur`, `content`, `content_md`, `created`, `created_ipaddress`, `updated`, `updated_ipaddress`, `updated_id_ur`, `deleted`, `deleted_id_ur`, `counter_replies`, `counter_saves`) VALUES
(1, 11, 0, 1, '<p>Welcome, uhm, God :)</p>\n<p>Feel free to send me a message if you need help with anything!</p>\n<pre><code>HELLO THIS IS GOD! Why can I edit your reply?\n</code></pre>\n<p>And can you edit my edit on your reply?</p>\n', 'Welcome, uhm, God :)\n\nFeel free to send me a message if you need help with anything!\n\n```\nHELLO THIS IS GOD! Why can I edit your reply?\n```\nAnd can you edit my edit on your reply?', 1466122954, 1269576253, 1466205238, 1398250368, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0),
(2, 12, 0, 1, '<p>Thank you for the suggestions! The off-topic board is a great idea. I will add that shortly.</p>\n<p>I''m not entirely sure we need a testing board, since anyone can start a board right now and test on their own. Also, it would be a little difficult to open up permissions on this one board only, so that anyone could modify the board''s settings. If things start getting cluttered up with abandoned boards then I''ll look into it, but for now, let''s see how it goes.</p>\n', 'Thank you for the suggestions! The off-topic board is a great idea. I will add that shortly.\n\nI''m not entirely sure we need a testing board, since anyone can start a board right now and test on their own. Also, it would be a little difficult to open up permissions on this one board only, so that anyone could modify the board''s settings. If things start getting cluttered up with abandoned boards then I''ll look into it, but for now, let''s see how it goes.', 1466152426, 1269576253, 1466152518, 1269576253, 0, 0, 0, 3, 0),
(3, 12, 2, 6, '<p>You are right about the testing board. I have noticed that I didn''t get any notification when you replied, is this by design, a missing feature or a bug?</p>\n', 'You are right about the testing board. I have noticed that I didn''t get any notification when you replied, is this by design, a missing feature or a bug?', 1466198469, 1427728197, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(4, 13, 0, 1, '<p>Interesting... Good to know, but unfortunately it''s a side affect of using Markdown. Reddit has the same issue, as will most other sites that use this format. Having said that, you can get around it by just using a normal anchor tag like you described.</p>\n<p><strong> UPDATE </strong> - Hmm, odd, the anchor tag works when I preview but it is lost after I save. I''ll have to look into this further. Thanks!</p>\n', 'Interesting... Good to know, but unfortunately it''s a side affect of using Markdown. Reddit has the same issue, as will most other sites that use this format. Having said that, you can get around it by just using a normal anchor tag like you described.\n\n** UPDATE ** - Hmm, odd, the anchor tag works when I preview but it is lost after I save. I''ll have to look into this further. Thanks!', 1466204311, 1269576253, 1466204754, 1269576253, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0),
(5, 11, 1, 5, '<p>I''m humbled, it''s our beloved admin visiting my board! /g/Music is hereby confirmed to be the best board.</p>\n', 'I''m humbled, it''s our beloved admin visiting my board! /g/Music is hereby confirmed to be the best board.', 1466205112, 1398250368, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(6, 12, 2, 1, '<p>The missing notification is by design, but I''m starting to think it was a bad idea. My original thought was you could keep track of new replies by just paying attention to the red "New Replies" counter on each topic, or by saving the topic and then sorting by "New Replies" on your User Dropdown &gt; My Topics page... but it''s starting to annoy me to have to constantly check those places.</p>\n<p>I''ll start looking into implementing reply notifications tonight.</p>\n<p>By the way, what do you think about the limit I have in place on replies (where it forces you to create a new topic after the 2nd level) ? You can see this by trying to reply to me. It was a bit of an experimental thing I wanted to try out, to see if it keep conversations on track and less cluttered... but I''m not sure how well received it will be.</p>\n', 'The missing notification is by design, but I''m starting to think it was a bad idea. My original thought was you could keep track of new replies by just paying attention to the red "New Replies" counter on each topic, or by saving the topic and then sorting by "New Replies" on your User Dropdown > My Topics page... but it''s starting to annoy me to have to constantly check those places.\n\nI''ll start looking into implementing reply notifications tonight.\n\nBy the way, what do you think about the limit I have in place on replies (where it forces you to create a new topic after the 2nd level) ? You can see this by trying to reply to me. It was a bit of an experimental thing I wanted to try out, to see if it keep conversations on track and less cluttered... but I''m not sure how well received it will be.', 1466206014, 1269576253, 1466206229, 1269576253, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(7, 13, 4, 6, '<p>&gt;Reddit has the same issue, as will most other sites that use this format</p>\n<p>While you are right about reddit, many popular sites that use Markdown don''t have that issue, StackOverflow doesn''t have that limitation (it used to have it but it was marked as a bug and fixed), the original implementation also fixed it and Voat never had that issue. GitHub flavored Markdown also doesn''t have it.</p>\n<p>The issue seems to depend a lot in the Markdown implementation you are using, replacing ( with %28 and ) with %28 seems to be a good enough workaround.</p>\n<p>This only appeared in the preview but after I posted it it seems to have fixed itself, are you using two different implementations, one for the preview and one for displaying posts/replies?</p>\n<p><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shebang_(Unix)">Test 2</a> (this appears broken in the preview, let''s see if it remains broken after I click "post reply").</p>\n', '>Reddit has the same issue, as will most other sites that use this format\n\nWhile you are right about reddit, many popular sites that use Markdown don''t have that issue, StackOverflow doesn''t have that limitation (it used to have it but it was marked as a bug and fixed), the original implementation also fixed it and Voat never had that issue. GitHub flavored Markdown also doesn''t have it.\n\nThe issue seems to depend a lot in the Markdown implementation you are using, replacing ( with %28 and ) with %28 seems to be a good enough workaround.\n\nThis only appeared in the preview but after I posted it it seems to have fixed itself, are you using two different implementations, one for the preview and one for displaying posts/replies?\n\n[Test 2](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shebang_(Unix)) (this appears broken in the preview, let''s see if it remains broken after I click "post reply").', 1466210194, 1389494547, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
