(10, 11, 0, 1, '<p>I hereby bestow the highly acclaimed, much sought after <strong> Best Board </strong> award to /g/Music !!!</p>\n<p>&lt;insert roaring crowds and ticker tape parade here&gt;  </p>\n<p>Well for now at least... who knows what boards will show up tomorrow!</p>\n<p>On a serious note, yes, as a board owner, you can edit anyone''s reply. You are, <em>cough</em>, God after all. I can also edit your edit on my reply, and so the endless circles begins... but this power should really only be used for minor updates in topics that are enforcing some kind of standard / templated reply (and the user maybe missed the memo on this). If the post really is against your guidelines then it would better to just delete the reply or message the user. Users can not restore a reply that was deleted by a moderator / board owner.</p>\n<p>Having said all that, you probably shouldn''t be able to edit my replies. I will be fixing that :)</p>\n', 'I hereby bestow the highly acclaimed, much sought after ** Best Board ** award to /g/Music !!!\n\n&lt;insert roaring crowds and ticker tape parade here&gt;  \n\nWell for now at least... who knows what boards will show up tomorrow!\n\nOn a serious note, yes, as a board owner, you can edit anyone''s reply. You are, *cough*, God after all. I can also edit your edit on my reply, and so the endless circles begins... but this power should really only be used for minor updates in topics that are enforcing some kind of standard / templated reply (and the user maybe missed the memo on this). If the post really is against your guidelines then it would better to just delete the reply or message the user. Users can not restore a reply that was deleted by a moderator / board owner.\n\nHaving said all that, you probably shouldn''t be able to edit my replies. I will be fixing that :)', 1466228813, 1269576253, 1466325171, 1269576253, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0),
