(12, 14, 0, 1, '<p>The reply notifications have been added. Let me know if you see any issues, thanks!</p>\n<p>Regarding the topic splitting, I am starting to agree. It splits too soon and makes it hard to follow the conversation. I like the idea of giving the user a choice, as well as letting moderators do it too.</p>\n<p>The problem I am having a hard time figuring out is what to do with the UI. I''m not a big fan of the endless nesting that Reddit does. It makes things too cluttered, and a structure like that can impact performance (i.e. having to load all that data at once)... but I''m not sure how else it could be done. I''ll need to mull this over a bit. Let me know if you have any ideas.</p>\n', 'The reply notifications have been added. Let me know if you see any issues, thanks!\n\nRegarding the topic splitting, I am starting to agree. It splits too soon and makes it hard to follow the conversation. I like the idea of giving the user a choice, as well as letting moderators do it too.\n\nThe problem I am having a hard time figuring out is what to do with the UI. I''m not a big fan of the endless nesting that Reddit does. It makes things too cluttered, and a structure like that can impact performance (i.e. having to load all that data at once)... but I''m not sure how else it could be done. I''ll need to mull this over a bit. Let me know if you have any ideas.', 1466235032, 1269576253, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0),
(13, 19, 0, 1, '<p>The envelope icon on the top-right will turn red, and if you click that and go to your <strong> Message Inbox </strong> you will see the notification.</p>\n', 'The envelope icon on the top-right will turn red, and if you click that and go to your ** Message Inbox ** you will see the notification.', 1466235237, 1269576253, 1466235256, 1269576253, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0),
(14, 14, 12, 6, '<p>You are right, the endless nesting can get pretty annoying and getting that part of the UI is not going to be easy. There are two options I''ve seen other sites implement:</p>\n<ol><li>WordPress: limited nesting, after a configurable amount of nesting it stops nesting replies and displays them like a flat forum would do.</li>\n<li>reddit: the nesting is not actually infinite, it is configured to split after a high number of replies (you could actually do this but choose a lower number). Example: typical long thread, <a href="https://i.sli.mg/dS7cDo.png">it prompts to "continue this thread"</a>, after clicking that link a new page loads displaying <a href="https://i.sli.mg/UtrlBM.png">only replies to that thread</a>.</li>\n</ol>', 'You are right, the endless nesting can get pretty annoying and getting that part of the UI is not going to be easy. There are two options I''ve seen other sites implement:\n\n1. WordPress: limited nesting, after a configurable amount of nesting it stops nesting replies and displays them like a flat forum would do.\n2. reddit: the nesting is not actually infinite, it is configured to split after a high number of replies (you could actually do this but choose a lower number). Example: typical long thread, [it prompts to "continue this thread"](https://i.sli.mg/dS7cDo.png), after clicking that link a new page loads displaying [only replies to that thread](https://i.sli.mg/UtrlBM.png).', 1466235828, 2147483647, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
